           <div type="translation" source="bib:Chhom2011_01"><!-- kuch: The term 'slave' should be understood as 'servant'. -->
 	<p n="1-6">Gho Kabhata, Gho <gap reason="lost"/>deva, Gho Śivaruci, Gho Thkān, Gho Bhāva, Gho Kanras, Gho Vara, Gho Kaṁprvat, Gho Śūnyasiva, Gvāl Kaṁpañ, Tai Kaṁvraḥ, Tai Laṅgāy, Tai Caṁvoḥ, Tai Dharmma, Tai Kanso, Tai Parikalpa, Tai Ame Ājya, a boy at the age of running <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>si rat</foreign></supplied>, a baby boy <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>si pau</foreign></supplied>; total 10 male slaves <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>gho</foreign></supplied>, an animal keeper <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>gvāl</foreign></supplied>, 6 female slaves <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>tai</foreign></supplied>, a boy at the age of running <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>si rat</foreign></supplied>, a baby boy <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>si pau</foreign></supplied>; grand total 19.</p>
              <p n="7-10">Sruk Caṁkā: Si Vrahma, Gho Dharmma, Gho Krau, Gho Agat, Gho Phnos, Gho <gap reason="lost"/>ṅ, Tai Chpoṅ, Tai Kaṁvrau, Tai Kansoy, Tai <gap reason="lost"/>, Tai Kandai, Tai Kaṁprāt; total: 6 male slaves <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>gho</foreign></supplied>, 6 female slaves <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>tai</foreign></supplied>; grand total 12.</p>
              <p n="10-17">Sruk Dhanirālaya: Si Kaṁpañ, Gho Pandan, Gho Thgap, Gho Kanlāc, Gho Kanteṅ, Gvāl Kanteṅ, Tai Kansoy, Tai <gap reason="lost"/>, Tai Panlas, Tai Kan-as, Tai Kaṁbhat, Lap Chpoṅ, Tai Laṅgāy, Tai Jvik, a boy at the age of running <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>si rat</foreign></supplied>, Tai Kan-a accompanied by a baby boy <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>si pau</foreign></supplied>, Lap Kaṁpat, Tai Thmās, Tai Kan-ū; total: 5 male slaves <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>gho</foreign></supplied>, an animal keeper <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>gvāl</foreign></supplied>, 10 female slaves <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>tai</foreign></supplied>, 2 male slaves <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>lap</foreign></supplied>, a boy at the age of running <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>si rat</foreign></supplied>, a baby boy <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>si pau</foreign></supplied>; grand total 20.</p>
              <p n="17-22">Sruk Lkaṁ Amoghapura: Si Thgap, Gho Vleṅ, Gho Kan-ī, Gho Kanroy, Gho Pavitra, Tai Kanhyaṅ, Tai kañjes, Tai Jvik accompanied by a baby boy <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>si pau</foreign></supplied>, Tai Kaṁvai accompanied by a baby girl <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>tai pau</foreign></supplied> called Phnos and a girl <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>tai rat</foreign></supplied> called Vleṅ; total: 5 male slaves <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>gho</foreign></supplied>, 4 female slaves <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>tai</foreign></supplied>, a girl at the age of running <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>tai rat</foreign></supplied>, a baby boy <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>si pau</foreign></supplied>, a baby girl <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>tai pau</foreign></supplied>; grand total 12.</p>
              <p n="23-25">The people from Dhana Jrāy <gap reason="lost"/>, Gho Thkān, Tai <gap reason="lost"/>day, Tai Kaṁvai accompanied by 4 children; total 7.</p>
              <p n="25-30">Sruk Udyāna in the region of Jeṅ Tarāñ:  Gho Kaṁpañ, Gho Śrī, Gho Saṅvār, Gvāl Thgap, Gvāl Kaṁvrau, Tai Utpala, Tai Panhāṅ, Tai Paṁnaṅ, Tai Kandeṅ, Tai Kantāñ, Tai Krau, Tai Kaṁvraḥ; total: 3 male slaves <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>gha</foreign></supplied>, 2 animal keepers <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>gvāl</foreign></supplied>, 7 female slaves <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>tai</foreign></supplied>; grand total 12.</p>
              <p n="30-31">Sruk Kṣetrālaya Bhīmapura: Si Astraśīva, Gho Śrī, Gho Bhāva, Gho<!-- kuch: The text may be continued in K.183-7. --></p>
